<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-21T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="1147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1147">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/254</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-21T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>157. Consul, Pieclras Negras, reports confiscation of American brewery
                            Sabinas and raid by five Mexicans, including two Carranza officers, on
                            American-owned ranch near Guerrero, and that it appears Governor
                            Coahuila has started vigorous campaign against Americans and their
                            property.</p>
                        <p>Insist that governor be immediately ordered to desist from anti-American
                            activities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>